# Server Actions & Data Validation

All mutations (inserts, updates, deletes) must go through **server actions**. All inputs must be validated with **Zod** and typed with TypeScript — never use `FormData` as a parameter type.

## Rules

- Every insert, update, and delete must be implemented as a server action (`"use server"`)
- All data passed to server actions must be validated with Zod before use
- Define a Zod schema and infer the TypeScript type from it — never write the type manually
- Never accept `FormData` as a parameter type in server actions

## Pattern

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
"use server";
import { z } from "zod";
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

const createDeckSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  description: z.string().optional(),
});

type CreateDeckInput = z.infer<typeof createDeckSchema>;

export async function createDeck(input: CreateDeckInput) {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthenticated");

  const parsed = createDeckSchema.safeParse(input);
  if (!parsed.success) throw new Error("Invalid input");

  await db.insert(decks).values({ ...parsed.data, userId });
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — FormData type, no Zod validation
export async function createDeck(formData: FormData) {
  const title = formData.get("title") as string;
  await db.insert(decks).values({ title });
}
```
